(70, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', '29P Schwassmann-Wachmann', '2002-07-29 07:00:00', '14.81', '', '22"', '02/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Rising gibbous moon makes detection of entire periphery of this very faint and "transparent" coma difficult; very large and faint~', ''),
