(76, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', '29P Schwassmann-Wachmann', '2002-08-09 07:00:00', '13.31 (*m2 = 14.04)', '', '1.4''', '07/09/16', 'none', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Continued flattened coma in the NNW 1/3, clearly delineated; flaring to opposite side much more pronounced tonight; coma appears very large with very diffuse perimeter and concentrated center (*m2 = 14.04ccd), but nucleus is LESS pronounced than on previous nights; high haze~', ''),
