(393, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 K5 (LINEAR)', '2002-07-27 07:00:00', '13.95', '', '10"', '06/09/16', '181', '0.31m SCT with SBIG STV/r237 - 320 x 200 @ 14.8 microns; 90sec. exposure; photometric measurement via direct CCD.', 'Comet is somewhat brighter tonight with a slightly more distinct nuclear brightening than previously noted; tail and coma maintain consistent brightness uniformity across total expanse.', 'linearK5_0727.jpg'),
