(424, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-11-30 08:00:00', '11.7 (*)', '', '0.9''', '07/09/16', '325', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'A beautiful sight, with a very straight/narrow spike in PA 325 deg. for over 3.2'' length; tail has faint broad widening away from central spike up to about 1.5'' from coma; strongly condensed with a (*) m2 = 13.3.', 'RX14_1130.jpg'),
(425, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-12-01 08:00:00', '11.2 (*)', '', '1.1''', '07/09/16', '320', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very distinct and bright stellar nucleus (*m2 = 13.1); tail in PA 320 with strong spike at that position (6.6'' length) and another in PA 322 deg. for about 1'' length; comet is brightening rapidly and development is equally rapid.', '02_RX14_1201.jpg'),
(426, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-12-03 08:00:00', '11.2', '', '0.7''', '05/09/16', '315', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Nice tail in spite of incoming heavy haze; the coma demonstrates a large, but highly concentrated nucleus (*m2= 14.56ccd); one fairly bright tail streamer in PA 315 for about 2.2'' length, then tail fans and dims significantly to the SW', '2001RX14_1203.jpg'),
(427, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-12-06 08:00:00', '10.8 (*)', '', '1.1''', '07/09/16', '330', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very nice 4.4'' long tail in PA 330 degrees, curving gently NW from the coma; comet shows a very compact and bright coma with nucleus m2 = 12.76 ccd.', 'linRX14_1206.jpg'),
(428, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-12-07 08:00:00', '12.5', '', '0.8''', '06/09/16', '315', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Sharp tail spike in PA 315d for about 3.5'' length; comet does not appear as bright tonight, even with more favorable conditions from 12-6-02', 'RX14_1207.jpg'),
