(432, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-12-14 08:00:00', '11.2', '', '', '', '', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Image showing 2001 RX14 in negative with galaxy 3726 to south; note the interesting extensions of the fanned tail very close to coma.', 'linRX14b.jpg'),
(433, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-12-15 08:00:00', '11.3 (*)', '', '1.2''', '08/09/16', '315 curving', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very prominent curving tail, 4.4''length, in PA 315 deg.; coma is very small and faint by comparison, with incredibly bright (*m2 = 13.1) and stellar nucleus; excellent deep sky conditions after moonset', 'RX14_1215.jpg'),
(434, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2002-12-21 08:00:00', '10.7 (*)', '', '1.1''', '08/09/16', '300', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very nice curved tail in PA 300 deg, stretches 2.2'' length in full moonlight; comet is incredibly condensed with stellar (*m2 = 12.1) nucleus; tail spikes in PA 290 deg and 315 deg', 'RX14_1221.jpg'),
