(569, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 O4 Hoenig', '2002-08-21 07:00:00', '*m2 = 10.41', '', '~1.5''', '07/09/16', '130', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Moonlight and haze is so strong that only a slight indication of tail is seen via ccd; **no m1 attempted** due to washout of dark sky by moonlight; nucleus is very distinct and clear tonight with *m2 = 10.41~', ''),
(570, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 O4 Hoenig', '2002-08-26 07:00:00', '*m2 = 12.02', '', '0.8''', '07/09/16', '78 (?)', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Very distinct and bright (*m2 = 12.02) nucleus clearly shown within uniformly diffuse round coma; m1 and detailed size estimates not reliable in gibbous moonlight; very distinct extension or short tail in PA 78deg. extends some 0.6''.~', ''),
(571, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 O4 Hoenig', '2002-12-15 08:00:00', '<19.2', '', 'n/a', 'n/a', 'n/a', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Stellar limiting magnitude under exceptionally good conditions = 19.5; no object possible matching astrometric positions in two tries', ''),
(572, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 O5 (NEAT)', '2002-08-01 07:00:00', '15.88 (m2?)', '', '4"', '08/09/16', 'n/a', 'Mag/Size est. via 10cm Refr./ other measurements with 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'A very difficult object, and confirmed via two blinks @ 04:50 & 05:20 UT; (* m2 @ 15.88?) some elongation noted E-W, distinctly stellar with only hints of coma', 'Neat05_0801.jpg'),
(573, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 O5 (NEAT)', '2002-08-08 07:00:00', '16.59', '', '11" oval', '04/09/16', '135 (?)', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Elongated most distinctly; diffuse with possible extension in PA 135d; not a difficult target but faint.~', ''),
(574, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 O5 (NEAT)', '2002-08-09 07:00:00', '17.65', '', '4-5"', '02/09/16', 'n/a', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Very small, clearly diffuse but nearly stellar; clear skies with incoming haze; becoming very difficult object.~', ''),
(575, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 P1', '2002-08-09 07:00:00', '16.82', '', '3"', '08/09/16', 'n/a', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'This comet was quite difficult to locate, with a very small angular motion and quite fainter than early ephemerides provide; object verified via motion over 40-min. period.~', ''),
(576, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 P1 (NEAT)', '2002-09-06 07:00:00', '18.05', '', '11"', '03/09/16', 'irreg.', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', '[Large and irregular coma, very diffuse with some degree of central brightening; very faint but easy mark]', ''),
(577, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q1 Van Ness', '2002-08-22 07:00:00', '16.65', '', '6"', '02/09/16', 'none', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Very nebulous and not as small as expected; comet is clearly diffuse, no central condensation; strong moonlight and very low in SE.~', ''),
(578, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q1 Van Ness', '2002-09-06 07:00:00', '16.7', '', '14"', '02/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', '[Quite diffuse, low in SE sky and difficult]', ''),
(579, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q5 (LINEAR)', '2002-08-30 07:00:00', '16.35', '', '9"', '02/09/16', 'none', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Comet is small but clearly diffuse and very open, no central condensation, very difficult object in rich star field.~', ''),
(580, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q5 (LINEAR)', '2002-09-01 07:00:00', '15.63', '', '6"', '05/09/16', 'none', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Comet easy to distinguish in rich star field, but quite small; open, round and quite diffuse.~', ''),
(581, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q5 (LINEAR)', '2002-09-02 07:00:00', '16.45', '', '12"', '02/09/16', '', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Comet is small but clearly diffuse and very open, no central condensation; skies 5/6~', ''),
(582, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q5 (LINEAR)', '2002-09-03 07:00:00', '16.37', '', '9"', '06/09/16', 'N/A', 'image/photometry via 0.31m SCT @ f/3.75; SBIG/STV ccd @ 320 x 300 pixels, 14.8/pixel (gain = 1 to reduce SN ratio). 90 second exposures, unprocessed. Photometry via computer direct (ccdSoft).', 'Comet is small but clearly diffuse and very open, some central condensation, clearly nebulous in a very rich star field~', ''),
(583, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q5 (LINEAR)', '2002-09-05 07:00:00', '14.9', '', '28"', '03/09/16', '270 (?)', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Coma is definitely elongated in an E-W orientation; quite bright and easy; diffuse with considerable irregularity.', '');
