(584, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 Q5 (LINEAR)', '2002-09-12 07:00:00', '14.04', '', '28"', '08/09/16', 'n/a', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Possible duplicity of this comet is noted with two equal magnitude (m2 = 18.63)components oriented precisely N-S; coma appears to be elongated in same orientation.', ''),
(585, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 R3 (LONEOS)', '2002-09-29 07:00:00', '17.7', '', '10"', '02/01/00', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is very open, diffuse and small; extremely difficult object.', ''),
(586, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 R3 (LONEOS)', '2002-10-01 07:00:00', '16.6', '', '14"', '02/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is diffuse with no central condensation; difficult.', ''),
(587, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 R3 (LONEOS)', '2002-12-01 08:00:00', '17.5', '', '12"', '03/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very open and diffuse but small; imaged over 1.5 hour; no central condensation', ''),
(588, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 R3 (LONEOS)', '2002-12-28 08:00:00', '17.2', '', '11"', '04/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Faint, showing as mag1 17.6 to 17.2 on three images in very dark and clear skies', ''),
(589, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-10-31 08:00:00', '16.3 (*)', '', '9"', '04/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'This is a very small and difficult comet, nearly stellar, imbedded in a very star-rich portion of the Milky Way. Appears to be mottled or even perhaps two-part in ccd image. (*) m2 = 18.7ccd', ''),
(590, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-11-06 08:00:00', '16.5', '', '11"', '04/09/16', 'elongated', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is quite small and appears elongated in a NW to SE orientation; fairly concentrated but no clear nucleus; difficult with haze and high cirrus.', ''),
(591, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-11-12 08:00:00', '16.2', '', '14"', '03/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is very small and without any central brightening; uniformly circular; difficult in star-rich field.', ''),
(592, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-11-28 08:00:00', '17.1 (n)', '', '6"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is incredibly small, and identified only through astrometric motion over 2 hours in rich star field. Star-like and dead on ephemeris positions. Strong moonlight to east.', ''),
(593, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-11-29 08:00:00', '16.7', '', '11"', '03/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet very faint, nearly stellar; astrometric measurements over 00:59 confirms.', ''),
(594, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-01 08:00:00', '16.9', '', '8"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is very tiny and star-like; astrometric motion over 40 minute interval, otherwise quite difficult to detect.', ''),
(595, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-01 08:00:00', '16.3', '', '7"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet very faint and stellar, with clear motion in 45-min. astrometric spread', ''),
(596, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-02 08:00:00', '16.8', '', '7-8"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is tiny and starlike; verified astrometrically over one hour, moving very close to 16.1 mag star rendering estimates difficult; only very slight diffusity and nearly stellar in appearance.', ''),
(597, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-03 08:00:00', '16', '', '8"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Virtually no morphological changes since previous night', ''),
(598, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-06 08:00:00', '15.7', '', '9"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small and star-like, showing perceptible motion over 1.2 hour span.', ''),
(599, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-07 08:00:00', '15.7', '', '9"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is only very slightly diffuse; nearly stellar and difficult without motion to verify', ''),
(600, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-08 08:00:00', '15.8', '', '9"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very difficult in spite of apparent easy magnitude; nearly stellar and in rich star field; confirmed astrometrically.', ''),
(601, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-11 08:00:00', '16.5', '', '10"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet appears nearly stellar and without nebulosity; confirmed astrometrically; poor sky conditions and difficult', ''),
(602, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-14 08:00:00', '15.4', '', '9"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is barely diffuse, nearly stellar; confirmed astrometrically', ''),
(603, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-21 08:00:00', '15.9', '', '11"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Nearly stellar.', ''),
(604, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-25 08:00:00', '16.1', '', '11"', '08/09/16', 'n/a', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small and nearly stellar; one hour astrometry.', ''),
(605, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-26 08:00:00', '15.9', '', '10"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small and nearly stellar; some nebulosity, round', ''),
(606, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-28 08:00:00', '16.7', '', '10"', '05/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Clearly this comet is fading rapidly, with little activity; very little nebulosity seen', ''),
(607, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2002-12-29 08:00:00', '16.8', '', '10"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is becoming very faint and nearly stellar in appearance; astrometrically confirmed', ''),
(608, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2002-10-27 07:00:00', '15.5 (*)', '', '16"', '06/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very difficult comet in strong light of gibbous moon; coma is uniformly bright and transparent, round, with strong starlike condensation (*) m2 = 17.3ccd.', 'Available'),
(609, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-07 08:00:00', '16.4', '', '14"', '04/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet was imaged over a two hour period, showing good motion to west and north; round and somewhat compact; no central condensation.', 'C2002_V1_1107.jpg'),
(610, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-08 08:00:00', '16.3', '', '0.18''', '03/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet shows perhaps some elongation in a near-N-S. Comet C/2002 V1 (NEAT) imaged with the ccd @ f/3.75 for 90 seconds. Showing perhaps a bit more nebulosity than on previous night, no central condensation.', 'V1_02_1108b.jpg'),
(611, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-10 08:00:00', '16.1', '', '18"', '03/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very bad conditions with high winds, limited exposures; comet is quite faint, small and diffuse showing very rapid motion nearly due west.', 'neat02_V1_1110.jpg'),
(612, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-11 08:00:00', '16.5', '', '16"', '04/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet appears considerably more compressed, smaller; measurements indicate a slight magnitude drop as well.', ''),
(613, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-12 08:00:00', '16.1', '', '14"', '03/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is round and faint; astrometry recorded. Seemingly a bit brighter than previous night', ''),
(614, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-13 08:00:00', '16.5', '', '15"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is displaying a very distinct stellar nucleus (m2=17.1), surrounded by a uniformly diffuse and bright coma.', ''),
(615, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-17 08:00:00', '15.3', '', '18"', '04/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Much brighter than previous observations; comet is highly compressed, but no central condensation noted; uniformly bright across entire coma; very nice motion in short period.', ''),
(616, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-19 08:00:00', '15.2 (*)', '', '18"', '04/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Imaged and measured in extremely bright skies with full moon very close by; nuclear (*m2) = 16.3 ccd; comet is maintaining brightness, but estimate is likely underestimated because of moonlight.', ''),
(617, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-22 08:00:00', '14.5', '', '1''', '04/09/16', 'none', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'This comet has brightened significantly over previous days and is quite conspicuous (ccd) in spite of full moonlight. A very distinct, stellar nucleus, otherwise coma is a uniform circular glow.', ''),
(618, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-24 08:00:00', '14.3', '', '0.3''', '07/09/16', 'spiral', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Incredible view of this comet, with a distinct corkscrew coma as shown via ccd image. Comet is highly condensed with large central condensation. A most unusual coma with an apparent "clockwise spiral" structure.', 'V1neat_1124.jpg'),
(619, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-27 08:00:00', '13.8', '', '0.5''', '04/09/16', '359', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very high thin clouds but comet appears somewhat condensed with no clear nucleus; impressions are that the comet is quite bigger than measured, perhaps brighter; spike tail nearly due north from coma.', ''),
(620, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-28 08:00:00', '13.5 (*)', '', '0.5''', '04/09/16', '355', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet appears highly compact, but detail is difficult in strong moonlight and frosty skies; short wide tail imaged in PA 355 deg; (*)m2 = 15.43ccd.', ''),
(621, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-11-29 08:00:00', '13.1 (*)', '', '0.7''', '05/09/16', '350', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Coma is very bright and concentrated, large; some central condensation (*m2 = 15.53ccd); tail is seen slightly in PA 350 deg, vague', ''),
(622, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-01 08:00:00', '12.1 (*)', '', '0.6''', '06/09/16', '260', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is very compact and with tightly compressed coma; some strong condensation (*m2 = 13.84ccd) indicated; a very faint extension seen in PA 260 deg, for about 0.5'' length, but otherwise comet is elongated in a south-westerly orientation.', '02_V1_1201.jpg'),
(623, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-02 08:00:00', '12.4 (*)', '', '0.3''', '06/09/16', 'difficult', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Imaged for positional measurements only; heavy haze and intermittent clouds throughout the morning; comet appears fainter and smaller, but due to conditions.', ''),
(624, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-12 08:00:00', '12.2 (*)', '', '1.0''', '05/09/16', '?', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Possible odd shape to this coma, with plumes(?) appearing to emanate at PA 90 deg. and curve (2) north and south of highly condensed (*m2 = 14.98) nucleus; however no tail seen; the appearance of a crescent coma', ''),
(625, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-06 08:00:00', '11.3 (*)', '', '3.0''', '08/09/16', 'questionable', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Very interesting view tonight,with large (3.0'' arc) and quite round coma, very vague but evenly bright; strong bright nucleus (*m2 = 12.8); there appears to be some degree of elongation of the coma in a west direction and perhaps some indications of the plumed nature seen on previous observation.', 'neatV1_1206.jpg'),
(626, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-07 08:00:00', '11.2', '', '0.8''', '05/09/16', 'plumes', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet appears to be exhibiting two distinct plumes, one in PA 115 deg, and another in PA 277; coma is very compact and bright; very little suggestion of tail', 'neatV1_1207.jpg'),
(627, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-08 08:00:00', '11.5', '', '0.3''', '08/09/16', 'none seen', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Imaged and measured in very poor (bright froze haze) conditions; comet is very strongly condensed (m2 = 15.48ccd) and does not exhibit much of a tail; the coma is interesting in that there is little or no gradient, quite uniformly faint across except at center.', ''),
(628, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-11 08:00:00', '12.3', '', '1.1''', '08/09/16', 'none seen', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet very low in sky and fog moving in; strong central condensation (*m2 = 15.44ccd) located dead central in coma, not offset as has been suggested. Note the very chaotic morphology of the coma see in the attached image.', 'neatV1_1211.jpg'),
(629, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-14 08:00:00', '11.2 (*)', '', '1.1''', '08/09/16', 'fanned', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Interesting appearance with either a "jetted extension to the SW of the nucleus or fan tail stretching from 270 to about 200 deg, about 0.7'' length; coma appears highly condensed (*m2 = 13.9) and quite irregular; moonlight and fog interfere greatly with detail', ''),
(630, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-15 08:00:00', '10.9 (*)', '', '~1.0''', '08/09/16', 'unknown', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Size and magnitude estimatees are very questionable with very strong gibbous moon very nearby; *m2 = 13.8', ''),
(631, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 V1 NEAT', '2002-12-21 08:00:00', '11.8 (*)', '', '1.5''', '08/09/16', '315 ?', '0.31m SCT/ccd....', 'Appears to be a very tenuous tail in PA 315 deg, stretching about 6'' length; comet is considerably condensed with m2 (*) = 12.53ccd); coma seen in image as uniform "halo" effect, quite large and vague.', 'neatV1_1221.jpg'),
