(890, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', '2P Encke', '2003-11-08 08:00:00', '15.6', '', 'n/a', '07/09/16', 'n/a', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Nucleus of 2P is now faded substantially and is not as condensed as in previous dates; very difficult as strong moonlight and comet on W. horizon; seemingly more diffuse nucleus creates much difficulty in astrometric assessments.', ''),
