(892, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', '2P Encke', '2003-11-14 08:00:00', 'm2=15.8', '', '~7.2''', '06/09/16', 'fan, 249 to 327', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is now very open with fanned projection (tail?) in PA 269 through 327 deg; total breadth of this is some 7.2'' in both extremes; nucleus is now mottled appearing and not as condensed nearly as before, somewhat nebulous', ''),
