(1473, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-11 08:00:00', '10.2', '', '3.3''', '07/09/16', '315 (streamers)', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet demonstrates three (3) distinct tail streamers all emanating from a central area at about 315 deg PA; longest about 6''length and is also the southern-most; (*m2 = 14.0ccd)', 'rx14_0111b.jpg'),
(1474, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-12 08:00:00', '10.3', '', '3.1''', '07/09/16', '~315', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Showing a very beautiful tail with three distinct streamers suspected earlier; image clearly demonstrates very thin and long streamers emanting from PA points 270, 300 & 320 deg.; tail appears to expand immediately west of the large coma.', 'rx14_0112.jpg'),
(1475, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-14 08:00:00', '10.3 (*)', '', '~ 1.7', '08/09/16', '320', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Strongly curving fanned tail continues in spite of very brigth moonlit skies; nucleus (*m2 = 13.6 ccd) is very star-like and distinctly pronounced.', ''),
(1476, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-15 08:00:00', '10.5 (*)', '', '2.0''', '08/09/16', '3 spikes', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Tail clearly demonstrates at least three and possible four "streamers." Actual computer measurements of 3 primary are: (PA & lengths) 285d, 5.1'' / 296.7d, 4.0 / 307.1d, 1.8'' and a 4th short spike is suspected. Images reveal positions similar if not same to previous observations; (*m2 = 14.2ccd)', 'rx14_0115.jpg'),
(1477, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-17 08:00:00', '10.9 (25cm refr.) *', '', '0.75''', '07/09/16', '315, 303 & 215 curved', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'The same tail streamers are measurable via computer densitometry: three notable: 312deg, 5.1length; 303deg, 6'' length; and a third that emanates from the coma at PA 218 and then curves sharply NW in a similar angle as the rest, like a bent plume. m1 is affected by very strong moonlight (*m2 = 14.2 ccd, 0.41m SCT as are tail measurements).', ''),
(1478, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-19 08:00:00', '11.3 (*)', '', '~1.4'' (moon)', '07/09/16', 'see below', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet measured in very strong fullmoonlight; coma dia. measurements likely affected, but three distinct tail streamers: PA 309deg / 4.2'' length; 288deg / 4.8'' length / 269deg / 3'' length, all gently curving northward; these are the same three that have been measured for several dates now; overall the comet appears to be changing very little', ''),
(1479, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-20 08:00:00', '~11.5 (*)', '', '~2.1''', '07/09/16', 'curving', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Tail still showing streamers characteristic in both length and position as previous observations indicate; (*m2 = 14.6ccd); total tail length is approx. 7.2'' in strong moonlight', ''),
(1480, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-21 08:00:00', '11.7 (*)', '', '0.3'' ccd', '07/09/16', 'note below', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Imaged in very bright moist, moonlit skies. *m2=14.8ccd; tail streamers persist as: PA 312 deg, 5.5'' length, PA 266, 2.0'' length; total tail extends about 6'', curving; NOTE that coma is elongated slightly askew from an E-W orientation', ''),
(1481, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2001 RX14', '2003-01-22 08:00:00', '11.7 (*)', '', '.35''', '06/09/16', '312', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Curving tail with strong segment that projects from W perimeter of coma due west (270d) for .75'', then curves sharply to PA 312 deg for 2.6''; (*m2 = 14.6ccd)', ''),
