(1713, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-02 07:00:00', '11.2 (*)', '', '38" x 29"', '04/09/16', 'n/a', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is still remarkably elongated to ellipse with major axis oriented nearly due N-S at this time; there is some differentiation between an inner and outer coma; *m2=13.6ccd', ''),
(1714, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-12 07:00:00', '10.8 (*)', '', '33 x 16"', '04/09/16', 'poss. 197', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'A possible tail spike in PA 197 deg., for 86" length; coma continues elliptical (33" x 16") in shape and oriented SE to NW; *m2=13.4ccd', ''),
(1715, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-14 07:00:00', '10.7 (*)', '', '33" x 19"', '05/09/16', 'elongated', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is still elliptical in nature (coma), and is 33" x 19" diameter; extreme ends of SE & NW coma appear jet-like or with spikes; *m2 = 13.5ccd; heavy clouds moving in and strong full moonlight', ''),
(1716, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-15 07:00:00', '11.1', '', '1.0'' x 0.5''', '07/09/16', 'elong.', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Coma is becoming more ellipsoidal through time, oriented nearly N-S at present; very bright (*m2 = 14.3ccd) central condensation', ''),
(1717, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-18 07:00:00', '10.2 (*)', '', '48" x 32"', '05/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Remarkable object, with strong elongation continuing in a nearly N-S ellipsoid; central 1/3 of coma is markedly differentiated in brightness and resembles a bright nuclear core of an elliptical galaxy; size measures 48" x 32", no tail and coma is quite even with slight detected irregularity (*m2=13.7ccd)', 't7_1018be.jpg'),
(1718, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-19 07:00:00', '10.1 (*)', '', 'elong.', '06/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is brightening rapidly; Interesting changes within coma: nuclear concentration is becoming less ellipsoidal while ellipse continues in both eccentricity and size for overall coma; *m2=12.7ccd and becoming nearly round with slight ellipse. Coma size is 50" x 32" oriented in SE to NW configuration without change from previous dates', ''),
(1719, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-21 07:00:00', '10.0 (*)', '', 'elong', '05/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Continues to be very interesting, with ellipsoidal coma consistent (48" x 34" dia.); no distinct nucleus but strong (*m2=13.5ccd) central condensation; eccentricity of odd coma seems to be diminishing slightly', 't7_1021c.jpg'),
(1720, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-22 07:00:00', '10.2 (*)', '', '50" x 35"', '05/09/16', 'poss. 182', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'A possible short hint of tail in PA 182 for the first time from this highly elongated (50" x 35") coma; *m2=13.5ccd.', 't7_1022b.jpg'),
(1721, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-23 07:00:00', '10', '', '47" x 35"', '06/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Eccentricity on coma is decreasing slightly; with inner 1/3 of coma highly concentrated and differentiated in brightness; no tail in composite images', ''),
(1722, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-24 07:00:00', '10.0 (*)', '', '50" x43"', '06/09/16', '', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet appears virtually unchanged from previous morning, with the exception that the eccentricity is diminishing somewhat; *m2=13.6', ''),
(1723, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-27 08:00:00', '10.9 (*)', '', '58" x 42"', '', '', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Coma is "blunted" on E. side or seemingly "notched" in undersaturated images; very curious darkening to this side; coma still elliptical and no sign of tail; (*m2=13.4ccd)', ''),
(1724, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-29 08:00:00', '9.9 (*)', '', '51" x 40"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Coma well differentiated in brightness between central 1/2 and outer perimeter; outer portions now becoming somewhat more transparent while the inner 1/2 is very concentrated (*m2=12.6ccd); elongation of coma continues, 51" x 40"', ''),
(1725, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-10-30 08:00:00', '9.9 (*)', '', '60" x 44"', '05/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Images reveal some irregularity stemming from perimeter of central "core" of this comet, and some indication of curving or spiral jets similar to those seen with 29P frequently; coma continues to be elongated, but is growing less so and the coma is becoming more uniformly bright; *m2=12.6ccd', 't7_1030a1.jpg'),
(1726, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-12 08:00:00', '9.7 (*)', '', '65" x 50"', '05/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Coma elongation continues (65" x50") while overall size grows; little change in brightness (*m2=12.8ccd) and overall morphology of comet seems consistent', ''),
(1727, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-02 08:00:00', '9.8 (*)', '', '63" x 48"', '07/09/16', '152', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Notable broad extension in PA 152 clearly indicative of some type of tail formation; this is expressed beyond the elliptical (63 x 48") coma which is continuing to increase in size; strong nucleus embedded (*m2-12.8ccd)', ''),
(1728, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-03 08:00:00', '8.9 (*)', '', '61" x 51"', '07/09/16', '145?', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Becoming quite bright; Very interesting developments on E. side of coma, with large indentation evident due E. of nuclear center of comet, appearing much as a "notch" out of the bright coma cloud; coma continues elliptical (61 x 51") with strong central conds. (*m2=12.9ccd)', ''),
(1729, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-04 08:00:00', '9.0 (*)', '', '66" x 58"', '07/09/16', 'SE', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Possible extension (broad) to SE of elliptical (66" x 58") coma; comet is growing in size and quite bright; note that center 1/3 is brightly differentiated against outer 2/3 of coma (*m2=12.8ccd)', ''),
(1730, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-08 08:00:00', '11.6 (m2)', '', '60" x 48"', '07/09/16', '151', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very distinct fanned and short extension noted centered in PA 151 deg; clearly evident in this direction and not opposite, even though ellipticity of coma continues; inner 1/2 of coma is now strongly developed and condensed', ''),
(1731, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-19 08:00:00', '8.9 (1)*', '', '72" x 64"', '05/09/16', '123', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very broad, thick tail now developing in PA 123 deg; does not extend much beyond elliptical coma which is aligned in same PA; *m2=11.5ccd, and m1 determined via 10x50 binoc.; impression that both nucleus and inner coma is bowed slightly', 't7_1119b.jpg'),
(1732, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-20 08:00:00', '9.0 (*)', '', '72" x 62"', '05/09/16', '124', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Appears that tail is developing nicely, quite broad coming from the elliptical head which measures 72" x 62" ellipse; *m2=11.5ccd); there appears to be jets or streamers emanating nearly due south from outer coma, particularly one at about 182 deg.', ''),
(1733, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-21 08:00:00', '9.0 (*)', '', '67" x 60"', '05/09/16', '130', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is bright, with continued elliptical coma; tail in PA 130 degrees, short; curving coma with large nucleus (*m2=11.5ccd)', ''),
(1734, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-22 08:00:00', '~9 (10 x 50)', '', '72" x 77"', '06/09/16', '126', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Tail is developing very nicely, but still short (1'' length in PA 126 deg.); coma is growing quite large, 72" x 77" and becoming less elliptical in time; slight arch to extension toward tail from center of comet (*m2=11.9ccd)', ''),
(1735, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-23 08:00:00', '8.9 (10x 50)', '', '72" x 61"', '07/09/16', '117', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet has developed a broad, short but expanding tail in PA 117, that stretches some 2'' from the NE perimeter of the coma; tail appears almost blunt to NE; coma continues elliptical (72" x 61") and slightly arched or bowed, with a strong jet or extension in the tail PA from the nucleus (m2=11.8; beautifully developing comet', 't7_b.jpg'),
(1736, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-24 08:00:00', '9.3 (*)', '', '72" x 64"', '05/09/16', '120', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Broad tail extends only a short distance in PA 120 deg; large arched coma is 72" x 64"; short ccd exposures reveal several "rays" emanating from SE perimeter of comet, in same PA as pr. side of tail', ''),
(1737, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-25 08:00:00', '9.4 (*)', '', '70" x 64"', '05/09/16', '121', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Development of comet seems to be rather at a plateau at this point; coma size (70" x 64") and shape is consistent for previous dates and magnitude also (*m2=11.5ccd); seems however to be increasingly concentrated with only a short hint of tail (PA 121 deg.)', ''),
(1738, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-28 08:00:00', '10.8 (m2)', '', '86" x 82"', '04/09/16', '108', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is developing at a very fast rate, with a very fine outer coma now clearly evident, making the overall diameter of this comet less elliptical than previously; the tail continues broad and blunt in PA 108 deg.; many fine streamers are noted on the SE quadrant ejecting in the same PA as the broad tail', ''),
(1739, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-29 08:00:00', '10.7 (m2)', '', '70 x 72"', '05/09/16', '109', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Tail is just as broad a wide head of comet, extends only a short distance in PA 109 deg, with several fine streamers emanating from SE edge of coma; little change from previous night; NOTE that very short exposures reveal a dark "notch" in inner coma on EAST side of nucleus; very conspicuous as if inner coma wraps around nuclear center and passes eastward; this is not seen in saturated images, but suspect that this is visible visually', 't7_Nov29.jpg'),
(1740, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-11-30 08:00:00', '10.5 (m2)', '', '72" x 84"', '04/09/16', '107', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Total expanse of comet''s coma is very evident via ccd on dark night, still elliptical at 72" x 84" and slightly bowed; tail projects for short distance at PA 107, but much longer gas tail, broad, suspected for much greater distance in around PA 100 deg.', ''),
(1741, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-01 08:00:00', '9.2 (*)', '', '79" x 90"', '04/09/16', '106', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'In spite of quarter moonlight, coma is huge on this comet, with tail (PA 106 deg.) wide at point of origin and very broad for a short distance; (*m2=10.9ccd and note that m1 via 10cm refr.)', ''),
(1742, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-02 08:00:00', '~9.0 (*)', '', '79" x 76"', '06/09/16', '102', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Tail is emerging more every day, presently in PA 102 for 4.7'' length; nuclear center is becoming somewhat more distinct, less disk-like but still is quite large (*m1=10.1ccd); very large (1.1'') coma, still elongated', ''),
(1743, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-07 08:00:00', '~8.5 (*)', '', '78" x 70"', '07/09/16', '99', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet is developing very nicely with very diffuse and broad tail now nearly due east (PA 99deg.); the nucleus of this comet is now WELL defined (*m2=11.6) and very contrasting to a very uniform and transparent coma that is much less elliptical than in previous months; some NE offset of coma from nuclear center is noted', ''),
(1744, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-08 08:00:00', '11.6 (m2)', '', '~70"', '07/09/16', 'see below', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet has two distinct tail components that are developing nicely within the past two days; these are not visible visually, but do show up distinctly via ccd: first is in PA 130 deg., and second at PA 355 deg, both appearing as tapering "streamers" emanting from distinct inner coma surrounding nucleus; very poor conditions with strong full moonlight and much scatter', ''),
(1745, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-11 08:00:00', '~8.7 (*)', '', '73" x 82" ccd', '07/09/16', '89', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet has developed a fine tail extending nearly due east of strong nucleus (m2=11.4ccd); nucleus is elongated and slightly arced N-S orientation. The is a pronounced plume from nucleus in PA 170 deg, curving eastward for only a short distance this visible with very short CCD exposures.', ''),
(1746, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-12 08:00:00', '~8.2 (*)', '', '90"', '07/09/16', '87', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Coma is now "tadpole shaped" with a large central buldge (90" diam.) and tapering broad tail in PA 87 degree traced for at least 7'' length in strong moonlight; very fine image with strong central conds. (m2=11.2ccd) and plume southward from nucleus; tail appears segmented about 0.7'' from outer coma', 't7_a.jpg'),
(1747, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-15 08:00:00', '12.1 (m2)', '', '1.1''', '07/09/16', '82', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Beautiful and broad tail now developing in PA 82 deg., at least 8'' length (ccd); nucleus is very well defined and appears slightly elliptical (N-S); m1 estimated via 10cm Refr. @ 8.7 visual; a very strong plume or jet at about PA 125 deg for a short distance inside of coma', ''),
(1748, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-17 08:00:00', 'm2=12.5', '', '75"', '07/09/16', '81', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very fine "tadpole-shape" tail forming now in PA 81 deg., tapering rapidly to about 7'' length; very condensed nucleus which seems to be getting fainter as comet is gaining in overall brightness', 't7_a.jpg'),
(1749, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-18 08:00:00', '~8.6 (*)', '', '75"', '07/09/16', '79', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very fine tapering tail in PA 79 deg., for about 6.5'' length in poor seeing; nucleus continues to fade slightly and become smaller in extended size while comet maintains about consistent brightness; *m2 = 11.6ccd, while m1 via 10cm Refr.', ''),
(1750, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-19 08:00:00', '8.7 (*)', '', '80"', '07/09/16', '79', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Beautiful inner coma detail beginning to emerge; fine plumes in direction of tail (79 deg. PA); tail stretches more than 8'' in ccd; *m2=12.1ccd and slowly fading as comet increasing in overall brightness', 't7_1219.jpg'),
(1751, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-20 08:00:00', '8.3 (*)', '', '72"', '07/09/16', '78', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very strong tail now developed in PA 78 deg., over 8'' length ccd; nucleus (*m2=11.3ccd) is much brighter than previous night and with elongation; comet is very near mag. 8.2 star, making excellent ccd brightness comparison possible; coma diameter is holding steady at near 1.25'' arc', ''),
(1752, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-12 08:00:00', '8.2 (*)', '', '87" x 65"', '07/09/16', '75', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very nice tenuous tail is now about 9'' length in PA 75 degrees, tapering rapidly in "tadpole" shape; there is a very distinct curving plume on the N. perimeter of the inner coma which arcs rapidly toward the east into the PA of the tail; strongly condensed (*m2=11.7ccd)', ''),
(1753, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-24 08:00:00', '8.2 (*)', '', '80" x 60"', '07/09/16', '75 deg', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Primary gas tail in 75 deg., with slight extention or spiked tail north from this and parallel; comet is static in overall size but brighter, both nuclear and total (*m2=11.0ccd); tail stretches about 9'' length and tapers to very fine point; proximity to 8.2 mag. star makes ccd photometry of comet very accurate.', ''),
(1754, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-25 08:00:00', '8.4 (*)', '', '70"', '07/09/16', '72', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Comet maintains morphology from previous night with secondary tail parallel and N. of primary gas tail in PA 70 deg., coma becoming very diffuse with strong central conds. remaining consistent in elliptical shape and brightness (*m2-11.2ccd)', ''),
(1755, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-30 08:00:00', '8.4 (*)', '', '68"', '07/09/16', '73', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Beautifully formed and very diffuse tail now in PA 73, stretching about 6'' length and rapidly tapering to point, even in strong moonlight; some filaments throughout the tail are noted; nucleus (*m2=11.7ccd) is now quite round and without previously noted ellipticity', ''),
(1756, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean H41', 'C/2002 T7 (LINEAR)', '2003-12-31 08:00:00', '11.3 (m2)', '', '75"', '07/09/16', '72', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Tail remains unchanged in PA 72 deg., for about 6'' in strong quarter moonlight; very extended coma (75" dia.) with a slight extension or swelling to the south of the nucleus, this perhaps being a looped portion of the tail', ''),
(1757, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-03 08:00:00', '17.7', '', '12"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small and close to star causing some difficulty in m1 estimates; nearly stellar and confirmed astrometrically', ''),
(1758, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean Mountain', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-12 08:00:00', '17.6', '', '13"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small and difficult in poor conditions with incoming high cirrus; confirmed astrometrically, and nearly stellar', ''),
(1759, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-06 08:00:00', '17.9', '', '9"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Appears quite stellar with no nebulosity; confirmed astrometrically', ''),
(1760, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-07 08:00:00', '17.6', '', '10"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Ver faint, difficult, nearly stellar', ''),
(1761, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-08 08:00:00', '17.8', '', '12"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small and difficult in very poor conditions; slightly nebulous, but very near steallar in appearance', ''),
(1762, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-09 08:00:00', '17.4', '', '12"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small and nearly stellar, no nebulosity; confirmed astrometrically', ''),
(1763, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-10 08:00:00', '17.7', '', '12"', '07/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very difficult in moist skies and high wind; very stellar and confirmed via astrometric span', ''),
(1764, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-11 08:00:00', '17', '', '<12"', '08/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Stellar in appearance, no nebulosity but skies are now a bit hazy; confirmed astrometrically', ''),
(1765, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-12 08:00:00', '17.6', '', '14"', '07/09/16', 'n/a', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very compact and nearly stellar; difficult object in some high haze', ''),
(1766, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Conway H43', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-03-27 08:00:00', '17.8', '', '11"', '05/09/16', 'none', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Stellar, with little or no nebulosity; confirmed astrometrically in deep clear morning', ''),
(1767, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO - Petit Jean', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-04-11 07:00:00', '17.4', '', '12"', '07/09/16', 'n/a', '0.41m SCT/ccd....', 'Very small, stellar; confirmed astrometrically', ''),
(1768, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'H41', 'C/2002 U2 (LINEAR)', '2003-04-21 07:00:00', '17.7', '', '14"', '08/09/16', 'n/a', '...0.41m SCT/ccd.......P. Clay Sherrod, (ASO - Petit Jean Mountain, H41)', 'Incredibly tiny and difficult, confirmed astrometrically; quite stellar', '');
