(2497, 'P. Clay Sherrod', 'ASO Petit Jean Mountain South - H45', '9P Tempel 1', '2005-07-05 07:00:00', '10.1 (*)', '', '49"', '06/09/16', '113', '0.41m SCT @ f/3.3 ccd', 'Attached is a non-enhanced single raw image(s) from both July 4 (pre) and July 5 (post) showing Comet 9P before and after Deep Impact from our observatory here on Petit Jean Mt. Note that the nuclear magnitude changed considerably more than the total magnitude of the comet after impact, brightening about 0.6m, while the total magnitude changed only slightly from 10.3 on July 4 to 10.1 on July 5; the overall size of the comet however has changed, with the coma appearing more extended and particularly "heavy" offset to the SW side of nuclear center, this effect clearly seen visually in moderate telescopes; the eccentricity of the coma is not shown well in images.', '[{"file":"\\/images\\/comets\\/ComA5D5BC6.jpg","params":""}]'),
